title: La Strada
overview: A care-free girl is sold to a traveling entertainer, consequently enduring physical and emotional pain along the way.

title: Kramer vs. Kramer
overview: Ted Kramer's wife leaves him, allowing for a lost bond to be rediscovered between Ted and his son, Billy. But a heated custody battle ensues over the divorced couple's son, deepening the wounds left by the separation.

title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Udaan
overview: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

title: Capharnaüm
overview: While serving a five-year sentence for a violent crime, a 12-year-old boy sues his parents for neglect.
stars: ['Zain Al Rafeea', 'Yordanos Shiferaw', 'Boluwatife Treasure Bankole', 'Kawsar Al Haddad']

title: Short Term 12
overview: A 20-something supervising staff member of a residential treatment facility navigates the troubled waters of that world alongside her co-worker and longtime boyfriend.

title: East of Eden
overview: Two brothers struggle to maintain their strict, Bible-toting father's favor.

title: Ace in the Hole
overview: A frustrated former big-city journalist now stuck working for an Albuquerque newspaper exploits a story about a man trapped in a cave to rekindle his career, but the situation quickly escalates into an out-of-control circus.

title: Vozvrashchenie
overview: In the Russian wilderness, two brothers face a range of new, conflicting emotions when their father - a man they know only through a single photograph - resurfaces.

title: Enemy at the Gates
overview: A Russian and a German sniper play a game of cat-and-mouse during the Battle of Stalingrad.

title: Requiem for a Dream
overview: The drug-induced utopias of four Coney Island people are shattered when their addictions run deep.

title: Babam ve Oglum
overview: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

title: Ladri di biciclette
overview: In post-war Italy, a working-class man's bicycle is stolen. He and his son set out to find it.

title: Judgment at Nuremberg
overview: In 1948, an American court in occupied Germany tries four Nazis judged for war crimes.

title: I, Daniel Blake
overview: After having suffered a heart-attack, a 59-year-old carpenter must fight the bureaucratic forces of the system in order to receive Employment and Support Allowance.

title: Fight Club
overview: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

title: On Golden Pond
overview: Norman is a curmudgeon with an estranged relationship with his daughter Chelsea. At Golden Pond, he and his wife nevertheless agree to care for Billy, the son of Chelsea's new boyfriend, and a most unexpected relationship blooms.

title: Scent of a Woman
overview: A prep school student needing money agrees to "babysit" a blind man, but the job is not at all what he anticipated.

title: Rebel Without a Cause
overview: A rebellious young man with a troubled past comes to a new town, finding friends and enemies.
